<subSubSection id="7338C26DDAB3C3C0C52D416EC42EBB99" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="variation">
<paragraph id="BCF301F7D5BCC19FAE03E9BC76461E6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D763EA0FB90BCB207FA3826A5EB34A22" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
Unlike the typical Japanese form with an entirely black metasoma (
<bibRefCitation id="5021C6AEF2DE504C2E655A09F30C14C0" author="Mitai, K" journalOrPublisher="Esakia" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="21 - 78" refId="B18" refString="Mitai, K, Tadauchi, O, 2013. Taxonomic study of the Japanese species of the genus Sphecodes (Hymenoptera, Halictidae). Esakia 53: 21 - 78" title="Taxonomic study of the Japanese species of the genus Sphecodes (Hymenoptera, Halictidae)." volume="53" year="2013">Mitai and Tadauchi 2013</bibRefCitation>
: 54, fig. 23), the studied male specimens from Sichuan have T1-T3 partially red-brownish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C695D43D44D724B1C8D3E25E56CA10C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FC186C9D814383B567238A0259566111" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A76DFFBF7E08976D091A80FDFD52881" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
The species is closest to the Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="A48F05D6BEB768F02CDC1DADF8082E55" authorityName="Wesmael" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes scabricollis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scabricollis">
<emphasis id="3A9D507769EEE400E30FFEECF62F84A6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Sphecodes scabricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wesmael, 1835, but female differs by denser and distinctly punctate T1 (versus shallow sparse punctures) and the male differs by shorter antennae with F2 1.5 times as long as wide (versus 1.7), and a dark, usually entirely black metasoma (versus red T1-T3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B2DCBF1236ADF780884F8514C02B715" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="distribution">
